// ============================================================
// DATAGLOW — Multi-Dialect SQL Translation Layer (Polyglot Workbench, Batch A)
// ============================================================
// A zero-dependency, zero-network, no-build SQL dialect adapter. It takes SQL
// written in one of five common warehouse dialects and rewrites the high-value,
// concretely-incompatible bits into the DuckDB SQL the in-browser engine
// actually runs. It is deliberately NOT a full SQL parser: like the sibling
// tokenizer in sql-highlight.js it works on the raw string with a small set of
// composable regex/string rules, and — critically — it first MASKS single-quoted
// string literals and comments so a rule can never corrupt a literal that merely
// looks like a dialect token (e.g. the word LIMIT or a backtick inside a string).
//
// It is a PURE string -> string function: no DOM, no DuckDB import, no state. So
// it is trivially unit-testable in Node and safe to import from anywhere.
//
// What each dialect actually needs (verified against a real DuckDB engine, not
// assumed — see test/sql-dialect-adapter.test.mjs):
//
//   duckdb    — no-op passthrough (this IS the engine's native dialect).
//   postgres  — mostly already compatible: `::type` casts, `ILIKE`, the `~`
//               regex operator, `||` concat, `SUBSTRING(x FROM a FOR b)`,
//               `DISTINCT ON`, `LIMIT ALL`, `E'..'` escapes all run unchanged in
//               DuckDB. The one common incompatibility handled here is the
//               case-insensitive regex operator `~*`, which DuckDB lacks —
//               rewritten to regexp_matches(lhs, rhs, 'i').
//   mysql     — backtick identifiers `col` -> "col"; `LIMIT off,cnt` ->
//               `LIMIT cnt OFFSET off`; IFNULL(a,b) -> COALESCE(a,b);
//               NOW() normalized to now(). (IFNULL/NOW happen to be accepted by
//               DuckDB too, but are normalized for a single canonical output.)
//   bigquery  — backtick-quoted, fully-qualified table refs
//               `project.dataset.table` -> the bare DuckDB table name;
//               SAFE_CAST(x AS t) -> TRY_CAST(x AS t);
//               CURRENT_TIMESTAMP() -> now() (the parenthesized form errors in
//               DuckDB; the bare CURRENT_TIMESTAMP is left alone since it works).
//   snowflake — double-quoted identifiers already compatible;
//               IFF(cond,a,b) -> CASE WHEN cond THEN a ELSE b END;
//               DIV0(a,b) -> a safe-division CASE (0 when the divisor is 0).
//   tsql      — TOP n -> a LIMIT n moved to the end of the statement;
//               [col] bracket identifiers -> "col"; GETDATE() -> now();
//               ISNULL(a,b) -> COALESCE(a,b).

